sources.title: Time, Full Speed! Part One
sources.description:
Part Two: https://youtu.be/F2jFtgKHDgU

A film based on the novel by Valentin Kataev. First five-year plan, about the construction of the Magnitogorsk metallurgical plant. The heroes of the film - builders, having learned about the world record of Kharkov concrete workers, want to get ahead of them. The construction site is engulfed in a grandiose competition, and the young Moscow journalist Semechkin is looking for a hero for his report...

Year of production: 1965

Director: Schweitzer Mikhail, Milkina Sofya
Screenwriter: Valentin Kataev, Schweitzer Mikhail
Composer: Georgy Sviridov
Cinematography: Naum Ardashnikov, Yuri Gantman
Production designer: Freidin Abram

Starring: Yanvarev Alexander, Semina Tamara, Gulaya Inna, Yursky Sergey, Kuravlev Leonid, Semenov Viktor, Volyntsev Yuri, Zobin Vadim, Kadochnikova Larisa, Kashpur Vladimir, Kopelyan Yefim, Koroleva Elena, Lavrova Tatiana, Muratov Radner, Oya Bruno, Victor Sergachev , Nikolai Fedortsov, Yevgeny Kharitonov, Stanislav Khitrov, Boris Yurchenko, Igor Yasulovich
